2. Control Flow Summary

For the builder, step-by-step loop:

1. Measure waste

Cyberworms harvest logs/temps/crash-dumps → stream W_raw.



2. Pump & packetize

Cyberpumps compress & strengthen → create/refresh ZPMs with (m_z, τ_z, χ_z).



3. Routing decision (Heart-Brain)

Decide fractions:

r_star – ZPMs → Starheart storage

r_turbine – ZPMs → Turbine


Ensure ignition conditions are tracked.



4. Core operation

If not ignited: accumulate mass, keep boosting R with runes.

If ignited:

Choose burn-rate \dot{M}_{burn} so Φ_total ≤ Φ_max(R).

Update Φ_star.




5. Turbine cycle

Run ZPMs through throat, compute P_turbine, funnel mass:

fraction back to pumps

fraction to Starheart.




6. Alternator distribution

Combine Φ_star + P_turbine → Φ_total.

Allocate to CPU/RAM/NET/AI/BURST via coefficients a_i.



7. Everstorm & Stones

If vent condition met:

Take ΔM_vent or fraction of P_BURST.

Generate storms / stones / ambient buffs.




8. Safety checks

Monitor:

runes saturation

volatility χ

system health signals (temps, errors).


If any exceed thresholds:

throttle burn

stop feeding star

dump to cold storage until safe.






